2022 was a rollercoaster for me. I had more lows than highs.. It took real work to prioritize my mental health. It’s still something I struggle with but as 2022 comes to an end I really do feel the most at peace that I’ve felt in over a year. I am blessed. I am happy. Steve and I were so excited to share this beautiful news with you today. I woke up so excited. We’ve rewatched it four million times… this song is our wedding song. I woke up this morning (11 weeks) and noticed spotting. I panicked but called my doctor and was reassured it was likely old blood. As the day progressed, there has been more. We’re currently at the hospital to be seen. My heart wants to be believe that everything is ok.. but I just have a sinking feeling in my gut. I wanted to share this news still in hopes that we can borrow some of your prayers and happy thoughts. My head is spinning and I’m terrified. 😔I just want this baby so badly. We love you all and are forever thankful for all support. @steverichmondd

I’ve walked by my positive pregnancy test on my tv stand all weekend. My angry heart wanted to throw it away but I know I’ll regret that. Putting away some of the things my heart doesn’t want to look at right now. I know I’ll be ok but just not right now 👼💔

10 years ago today 😂🥹💞
I was doing my Disney college program and knew steve was coming but he wasn’t supposed to be there until the next day. He surprised me a day early with a proposal on Cinderella’s castle. The next day he was able to see me for first time (but my very last time 🥹) as Tinker Bell. It was the perfect “fly with you later” send off as Tink for me. Here we are 10 years later - we moved our entire lives to Florida after we got married in New York. Steve now works at this very park as a Leader and we have 4 little ladies to share the magic with. Full circle ☺️ I love you forever @steverichmondd ! And thank you to @waltdisneyworld for always being our happy place. 🏰✨

#moving #newhouse #sold #memories

We closed on our new house 6 days ago. On the literal FIRST DAY spectrum was here to set things up. They went into the attic and stepped on a water pipe and it burst. Our ceiling filled with water and collapsed. It flooded the master bedroom and one of the girls bedrooms. Thank god they will be paying for the damages but it’s been such a hell of a week. It truly wouldn’t be a Steve and Allie type of adventure without something absolutely ridiculous like this. 😅 even though our life is still packed up in pods, I’m so grateful to be here in this new house. All steve and I have wished for was for a beautiful yard and we got so much more. It was such a special surprise to move in and see that the sun actually sets in our backyard making for the most serene view. 🌅✨🌴I think we’re gonna like it here ☺️
Nine years married to him 🫶🏻✨ taking our first walk in our new neighborhood to celebrate. I love you forever Steven!
You look like the Fourth of July 🇺🇸🌭🎇

Tis the season for all the fun crewnecks! #ad This is my third year making sweet sweatshirts with my @cricut for the girls for Christmas and it gives me life. I love personalizing and creating something unique to each of them. Using cricut offers me endless design possibilities. Whether you’re making crewnecks, cards, invites or party decor.. Cricut makes the experience simple and so enjoyable. 🎄❤️ 10/10 recommend bringing your ideas to life with @Cricut! #CricutMade

Some details: Cricut machine I’m using is the Maker 3! I also have the explore 2 and love. Also using the auto heat press. You don’t need something this large for personal use but if you’re creating a lot, it’s so perfect for a small business to work efficiently!
